Rebrand code-server surfaces to Composery (identity, env vars, paths, assets, theme)

Single patch covering every front-facing code-server -> Composery rename, merged
from the former rebrand-product/env-vars/paths/assets/theme-cache patches:

- product.json identity and links (ci/build/build-vscode.sh): nameShort/nameLong
  -> "Composery" (tab, window, About), serverDataFolderName -> ".composery-server",
  and report-issue/docs/license/tips/videos/newsletter links -> Composery. Internal
  ids (applicationName, win32/darwin, keyboard-shortcut PDFs) stay code-server.
- env vars (src/node/cli.ts, http.ts, main.ts, wrapper.ts): every CODE_SERVER_*/CS_*
  var and the {{CS_STATIC_BASE}} template token -> COMPOSERY_* namespace, no fallback,
  so the code-server name can never leak into operator config. Paired overlay HTML
  uses {{COMPOSERY_STATIC_BASE}}.
- user-data paths (src/node/util.ts, cli.ts): config/data/extensions dir code-server
  -> composery (settings.json under ~/.local/share/composery, config under
  ~/.config/composery) and the PWA install name defaults to "Composery".
- product logo and letterpress (lib/vscode .../code-icon.svg + editor/sessions
  letterpress svgs): VS Code mark and empty-editor/sessions watermarks -> Composery
  icon. Patched in source, not overlaid, because the minified build relocates them.
- theme cache (lib/vscode .../workbenchThemeService.ts): force one
  reloadCurrentColorTheme() after init so a rebuilt Composery theme overrides the
  colours VS Code persists in browser IndexedDB.

The CLI binary, IPC socket/mutex names, /tmp scratch dir, version coordinates, and
upstream coder/code-server URLs are intentionally left untouched (build/runtime
machinery, never user-visible). See README "Branding rename policy".

